Winter Olympics 1992:
   Games Stats: Figure Skating
-- Number of times a backflip has been performed in men's
singles competition: 1 (after American Terry Kubicka did it
at the 1976 Innsbruck Games, the move was banned as too
dangerous).
                                                                                                       

   -- Age at which Sonja Henie began competing in the Olympic
Games: 11.
                                                                                                       

   -- Estimated fortune Sonja Henie earned by skating in ice
shows and motion pictures: $50 million.
                                                                                                       

   Compiled by Olympics Factbook, Visible Ink Press, a
division of Gale Research, Detroit.